<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n35236a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35236a">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35236a"> 236(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> jake bow / Sheaf &amp; Sallet</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The acquisition of the freedom of the city entailed certain duties upon the citizens, prominent amongst which was that of taking part in the defence of the city. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> This duty was brought home to the freeman at the time of his enrolment as is evidenced by a law made by the Common Council in the year 1454, recorded in the Calendar of Ancient Records of Dublin as follows: &ldquo;Also, hit was ordenyte and stabled in the said semble that no prentise of merchande shulde be admitted unto the fraunches of the said citte till he have a <mark>jake bowe, shefe, sallet</mark> <font color="green">[a light helmet]</font> and swerde <font color="green">[sword]</font> of his own <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rdquo; <small> John J. Webb, <a name="JJWG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JJWG"><cite title="source">The Guilds of Dublin</cite></a> (Jun 1929) 123</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
